Philippine Stocks: Abra, Greenergy, Lepanto, Philex Petroleum

-- B y   I a n   C .   S a y s o n   a n d   C h a n   T i e n   H i n
-- 
2011-09-12T05:39:14Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-12/philippine-stocks-filinvest-land-lepanto-consolidated-philex.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in Philippine trading. Stock symbols are
in parentheses and prices are as of the noon close in  Manila .  The Philippine Stock Exchange Index fell 1.2 percent to
4,296.05, its second day of losses.  Index-related stocks:  Lepanto Consolidated Mining (LC)  Corp.’s
Class-A shares (LC PM), which are reserved for Filipinos, sank
4.9 percent to 1.35 pesos, the first loss in three days. Its
Class-B shares (LCB PM), which have no ownership restrictions,
declined 4 percent to 1.45 pesos, the lowest since Aug. 10.
 First Philippine Holdings Corp. (FPH)   declined 1.1 percent to
56.35 pesos, the lowest since March 30.  Security Bank Corp. (SECB) 
 decreased 1.2 percent to 90 pesos, the lowest since
Aug. 9. Lepanto, First Philippine and Security Bank are among
five stocks that the exchange will remove today from the
nation’s benchmark equities index.  Abra Mining & Industrial (AR)  Corp jumped 10 percent to
0.55 centavo, the highest close since November 2009, after the
company said its board authorized a joint-venture agreement with
Olympus Pacific Minerals Inc. for the development of a mining
asset.  Greenergy Holdings Inc. (GREEN PM) slumped 7.7 percent to
1.2 centavo, after the company’s board approved the sale of 5.5
billion shares through a so-called private placement at 1
centavo a share.  Philex Petroleum Corp. (PXP PM), the petroleum unit of the
largest Philippine metals producer, jumped to 8.60 pesos,
valuing the company as the nation’s second-biggest oil exporter,
after 1.7 billion common shares were listed on the stock
exchange at 1.20 pesos each.  Philex Mining Corp. (PX)  , which
owns the company, increased 0.4 percent to 27.10 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ian C. Sayson in Manila at 
 isayson@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
